    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>[Your Company Name] ("we", "us", or "our") provides a GPT-based service that integrates with third-party tools like Google Sheets via Make.com ("Service"). This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, share, and protect information when you or others use our Service.</p>
    <p>By accessing or using the Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect several types of information in connection with the use of our GPT and its integrations:</p>

    <h3>1. Personal Information</h3>
    <p>While interacting with the GPT, we may collect personal information such as names, email addresses, or other identifiers when explicitly provided by users.</p>

    <h3>2. Usage Data</h3>
    <p>We collect information about how the Service is used. This may include IP addresses, device types, browser types, interaction logs, and other diagnostic data.</p>

    <h3>3. Data Submitted via the GPT</h3>
    <p>When users interact with our GPT, any information they provide during the session (e.g., form data, text inputs) may be transmitted to and stored in third-party services like Google Sheets via Make.com. This may include sensitive data depending on what users input into the GPT.</p>

    <h3>4. Third-Party Integration Data</h3>
    <p>Our GPT uses Make.com to integrate with services like Google Sheets. As a result, information submitted via the GPT is transmitted to those third-party services, where it is processed and stored. We do not control how third-party services handle your data and recommend reviewing the privacy policies of these services.</p>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We may use the information collected for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>To facilitate the operation of our GPT service and fulfill user requests.</li>
        <li>To transmit data to connected services, such as posting data to Google Sheets via Make.com.</li>
        <li>To monitor and improve the Serviceâ€™s performance, reliability, and user experience.</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations and resolve any disputes or security concerns.</li>
    </ul>

